properties.name: Beijing, China
properties.description: Posted by AkikoackyBeijing, ChinaI went there a couple of years ago and many buildings were being constructed prepering for Olympic 2008. The Great Wall was so amazing, needless to say.

properties.name: Huhehaote, China
properties.description: Posted by AkikoackyHuhehaoteThis is in Inner Mongoria, a part of China. However, culture there is mongolian and you can see both Chinese and Mongolian on signs in th city. There were huge grassland. People there eats lamb and can ride a horse.

properties.name: Kayseri, Turkey
properties.description: Posted by AkikoackyKayseriThis is near Cappadocia, one of the famouse world heritage site.

properties.name: Key West, FL
properties.description: Posted by Akikoacky, , FLI went there last spring break. It was really beatiful and people are laid back. key west is so small island that I could went around by bike. There were Dolphins in the sea.

properties.name: Miami, FL
properties.description: Posted by AkikoackyMiami, FLI went there last spring break. The beach was so beautiful. There are many people who speak spanish.

properties.name: Okinawa, Japan
properties.description: Posted by AkikoackyokinawaThis is an island located southern part of Japan, and has really beautiful coral sea around it. There is unique culture here, totally different from that in Honsyu.

properties.name: Portland, OR
properties.description: Posted by AkikoackyPortland, ORPortland is one of the cities I traveled during winter break. This city is environment-friendly. The town was so clean.

properties.name: Siemreap, Cambodia
properties.description: Posted by AkikoackySiemreapI went there to visit Angcor Wat. It is so amasing heritage, but it is confronted with land subsidence because of rapid tourism development.

properties.name: Toronto, Canada
properties.description: Posted by Akikoacky1255 Queen Street West, Toronto, ONI went there last November to visit my friend. This place is really cool because of ethnic diversity. People\'s accents are differnet one by one. I went to Niagara Falls, too.

properties.name: Vancouver, BC, Canada
properties.description: Posted by Akikoackyvancouver, bc, caI went there twice in 2002 and in 2005. This is the first place I went abroad by myself. I studied English at English school for about 3 weeks. I went there secound time with my mom to see my brother.

properties.name: Victoria, BC, Canada
properties.description: Posted by AkikoackyVictoria, BC, CanadaThis is one of the most beautiful island, I think. The town was clean, and there are beautiful flowers all around the town. People were so nice, too.
